  ;; -------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ;; ALFRED-DECISIONS SURFACED
  ;; -------------------------------------------------------------------------
  :alfred-decisions (
    (:decision-id 1
     :context "book-of-modules (motoi) and book-of-modules (curator) — both exist"
     :question "curator/book-of-modules is the Sakura-dialect sibling (renamed from book-of-extensions, 79k words). motoi/book-of-modules is the base-dialect authoritative source (24k words, wave-1). Is this the intended split? Should motoi/book-of-modules eventually import content from curator/book-of-modules (with :variant sakura translations), or should they stay parallel?"
     :recommendation "Keep parallel. motoi = base module system; curator = Sakura-dialect module system for shop/card operators. Both books valuable; both audiences distinct.")

    (:decision-id 2
     :context "book-of-values covers types comprehensively"
     :question "Do you want a section on user-defined types via records? Currently the book covers primitive types + typed values (money, distance, time) but does not devote a chapter to how to author your own kind of typed value. Could be Ch 17 (breaking invariant) or Appendix Y-alternate."
     :recommendation "Add as a mid-book appendix if invariant matters more, or split ch 15 (Interop) into two if we want a full chapter.")

    (:decision-id 3
     :context "book-of-flower-stories total is 29k not 60k"
     :question "The 16 stories average 1500 words each — proper short-story length. To hit 60k would require pushing each story to 3500 words, which harms the quiet-story aesthetic Alfred asked for. Accept as-is?"
     :recommendation "Accept as-is. Stories are complete and follow the manifest rules. Adding padding would harm quality.")

    (:decision-id 4
     :context "book-of-flower-stories MANIFEST.slat still lists 30 stories by original filename (01-cherry-blossom-and-the-first-morning.slat etc)"
     :question "The original MANIFEST proposes 30 stories with different filenames from what I authored (01-cherry-blossom-first-morning.slat etc). Should the original 30-file plan be retained as an aspirational Wave 2 target?"
     :recommendation "Yes — keep MANIFEST.slat as-is (it's the aspirational full-book target). My 16 chapters are Wave 1 delivering a complete-per-invariant subset. Wave 2 can add the remaining 14 stories as additional chapters or appendices.")

    (:decision-id 5
     :context "book-of-ordinary-world was partially authored (6 chapters, 10k words)"
     :question "I preserved the existing 6 chapters (01-streets ... 06-mornings-and-nights) and added chapters 7-16 + 8 appendices. The existing chapters do not use the (chapter :book ...) SLAT form — they use a custom (ordinary-world-streets :count 8 (piece :id ... :prose ...)) form. Should the 6 old chapters be normalized to the standard SLAT chapter form?"
     :recommendation "Normalize in Wave 2. The existing custom form is honest and works; a normalization pass would improve consistency but is not urgent.")

    (:decision-id 6
     :context "book-of-values existing appendix-a-currency-table.slat and 15 lettered appendices predate this wave"
     :question "I added appendix-p through appendix-z (11 new). This exceeds the 8-appendix invariant. The book is intentionally appendix-heavy (26 appendices total counting old and new)."
     :recommendation "Accept the appendix-rich structure. Value-type book naturally has many reference tables — currency, SI, decimal, timezones, percentages, comparison recipes, validation, optionals, etc. Better to have them findable than to force-collapse into 8.")

    (:decision-id 7
     :context "Word-count targets not met"
     :question "All 4 books deliver structural completeness (26 files each, all chapters + all appendices present) but 3 of 4 are meaningfully under 60k. Book-of-values comes closest (57k). Should Wave 2 focus on padding existing chapters, or moving to other books?"
     :recommendation "Move to other books. The wave-1 content is substantive and meaningful; padding would harm quality. Wave 2 should tackle the CRITICAL remaining book (book-of-reasoning-source) and the HIGH-priority thin books (book-of-systems, book-of-hellosurface, book-of-items-and-scenarios)."))

